  "text": "The photoaffinity probe N-(4-azido-2-nitrophenyl)-2-aminoethyl sulfonate (NAPtaurine), when present in the outside medium, inhibits chloride or sulfate exchange by binding to a site that is distinct from the chloride transport site asymmetric distribution of unloaded transport sites, Eo and E;, even when Cli = Cl. [CITATION_1] . As shown in the Appendix, Eq . A5, the ratio of Eo to E; under these conditions can be defined as the asymmetry factor, A.",
